# .rationale_cache.json is deliberately NOT ignored (changed 2026-07-20).
#
# It was ignored as "runtime-generated, regenerates on first request per
# company" -- true for the original click-through-the-Streamlit-app flow, but
# it silently broke the frontend: export_for_frontend.py reads this cache to
# populate each company's rationale in companies.json, and CI checkouts never
# had the file. So every daily_price_refresh.yml run regenerated companies.json
# with rationale=null for all 2,046 companies and pushed that to the live site,
# wiping every rationale that had been generated. Confirmed by diffing the
# workflow-pushed companies.json against a local export: 32 rationales present
# locally, all null in the deployed copy.
#
# It is also not cheaply "regenerable": at ~2,000 companies across three
# rate-limited free tiers it costs hours of API calls, so it's expensive derived
# data that belongs in version control, not a disposable cache.

# concurrency-safety sentinels for .rationale_cache.json (2026-07-22) --
# machine/run-local, never meant to be committed.
.rationale_cache.json.lock
.batch_generate_rationale.pid
